  "prompt": "What is demography?",
  "response": "Demography is the statistical study of populations, especially human populations. It involves analyzing and examining various characteristics of a population, such as:\n\n1. Size\n2. Structure\n3. Distribution\n4. Population density\n5. Birth rates\n6. Death rates\n7. Migration patterns\n8. Age composition\n9. Gender ratios\n10. Ethnicity\n11. Income levels\n12. Education levels\n\nDemographers use this information to:\n- Understand population trends\n- Predict future population changes\n- Inform policy decisions\n- Support social and economic planning\n- Help businesses and governments make strategic decisions\n\nThe field of demography uses data from census records, surveys, and other statistical sources to create comprehensive population profiles and projections.",
